Package civitas.celestis.util.array

Class DoubleArray

java.lang.Object
civitas.celestis.util.array.DoubleArray
All Implemented Interfaces:
SafeArray<Double>, Serializable, Iterable<Double>
public class DoubleArray extends Object implements SafeArray<Double>
A type-safe array whose elements' types are bound to the raw primitive double. Elements are stored in their primitive form, reducing the overhead of boxed Doubles. Double-typed arrays are designed with speed as their first priority, and are not thread-safe.
See Also:

    • cast

      @Nonnull public <F> SafeArray<F> cast(@Nonnull Class<F> c) throws ClassCastException
      Explicitly casts each element of this array to the provided class c, then returns the resulting array. The provided class c must be a superclass of this array in order for this operation to succeed.

      Unlike FastArray, a shallow copy is performed in the process, and changes in the new array will not be reflected to this array.

      Specified by:
      cast in interface SafeArray<Double>
      Type Parameters:
      F - The type of element to cast to
      Parameters:
      c - The class of which to cast the elements of this array to
      Returns:
      The resulting array
      Throws:
      ClassCastException - When at least one element of this array is not an instance of the provided class c
